==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poem
<hw>Po"em</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>po⟦eum⟧ma</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to make, to compose, to write,
especially in verse: cf. F. <ets>po⟦eum⟧me</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A metrical composition; a composition in verse written in certain
measures, whether in blank verse or in rhyme, and characterized by
imagination and poetic diction; -- contradistinguished from
<xex>prose</xex>; <as>as, the <ex>poems</ex> of Homer or of
Milton</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A composition, not in verse, of which the language
is highly imaginative or impassioned; <as>as, a prose <ex>poem</ex>; the
<ex>poems</ex> of Ossian.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poematic</ent>⟦br⟧
